---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout title="Is AD a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 3 Points)" description="AD is a valid Scrabble word worth 3 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. Short for advertisement. Learn extensions like ADS, ADD, ADO and strategy tips." keywords="is ad a scrabble word, ad scrabble, ad valid scrabble, ad points scrabble, two letter a words, ad meaning scrabble">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Is AD a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 3 Points)","description":"AD is a valid Scrabble word worth 3 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. Short for advertisement.","datePublished":"2026-06-29","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-ad-a-scrabble-word"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is AD a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, AD is valid in both TWL (North American) and SOWPODS (International) Scrabble dictionaries. It scores 3 points (A=1, D=2) and is short for advertisement."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What words can you extend AD into?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"AD extends into many useful words: ADS (4pts), ADD (5pts), ADO (4pts), ADDS (6pts), ADZE (14pts). ADZE is particularly valuable with the Z tile scoring 10 points."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"When should I play AD in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Play AD when you need to dump a D tile for rack balance, set up an extension like ADZE on your next turn, or create a parallel play for cross-scoring. AD is also useful in tight endgame board positions."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/two-letter-words/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Two-Letter Words</a>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is AD a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 3 Points)</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>3 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Yes, AD is a valid Scrabble word worth 3 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. It's the informal shortened form of "advertisement." With D worth 2 points, AD gives you a reliable 2-letter play for rack management and setting up extensions like ADD and ADZE.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-green-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-950/30 to-emerald-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-green-500/70">✓ VALID</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">AD</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-green-300 font-semibold mb-3">3 points · A=1, D=2 · An advertisement (informal)</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Valid in both TWL (Tournament Word List) and SOWPODS (Collins Scrabble Words). AD is a common abbreviation that entered the dictionary as a standalone noun meaning a public notice or paid announcement.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Both</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TWL + SOWPODS</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9 A-tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">In the Bag</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4 D-tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Available</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">AD Extensions: Build Bigger Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ADZE</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ADD</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ADS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">4pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ADO</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">4pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ADDS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ADMIT</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">AD Strategy: When to Play It</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">D-tile dump:</span> With 4 D-tiles in the bag, you'll often draw duplicates. AD lets you offload one D while keeping your rack balanced for bingo-hunting next turn.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Setup for ADZE:</span> Play AD near a spot where Z can reach. ADZE (14pts) is a powerful extension — the Z on a DLS alone makes it 24 points.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Front-hookable:</span> AD has 10 front hooks — BAD, DAD, FAD, GAD, HAD, LAD, MAD, PAD, SAD, TAD. Your opponent may extend it for you, giving you cross-scoring opportunities.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Did You Know?</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">AD is one of the most <span class="text-white font-medium">front-hookable 2-letter words</span> in Scrabble. Ten different letters can attach to the front: B, D, F, G, H, L, M, P, S, T. This makes it both useful to play and risky to leave open for your opponent.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/is-er-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is ER a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/is-ta-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is TA a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up required</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
